TITLE
Housing Energy Performance & Retrofit Simulation (King’s Lynn & West Norfolk)
INTRO
This project explores housing energy performance using publicly available EPC data and simulates how targeted retrofit investments could improve energy efficiency across properties.

What the project does:
Analyses current EPC ratings across properties
Identifies areas with low energy performance
Simulates potential EPC improvements
Models a £5M retrofit budget scenario

Tools used:
Python (Pandas, NumPy)
Power BI
Public EPC dataset

Key Insight:
The simulation shows that a targeted investment approach could upgrade hundreds of lower-rated properties, shifting overall performance toward EPC band C.

Files in the repo
epc-retrofit-analysis.ipynb → data cleaning + simulation
epc_enriched.csv → full dataset with predictions
funded_homes.csv → budget-selected properties

